      "content": "It's generally not recommended to take simvastatin and clarithromycin at the same time, as they can interact and increase the risk of muscle damage. The FDA has warned about this risk, particularly when taking statins and certain antibiotics like clarithromycin. To minimize the risk, you should take your simvastatin at least 2 hours before or after taking clarithromycin. However, it's always best to consult your doctor or pharmacist for personalized advice.",
